     ('A recession is formally defined as',
      ['A 10% decline in the stock market', 'Two consecutive quarters of negative real GDP growth', 'Rising unemployment for six months', 'A decline in consumer spending']),
     ('The unemployment rate is classified as a lagging indicator because',
      ['It is measured less frequently than other indicators', 'It continues to rise even after a recession ends, as firms delay hiring until recovery is certain', 'It predicts recessions before they occur', 'It measures the same thing as real GDP']),
     ('Potential GDP represents',
      ['The absolute maximum output the economy could produce', 'The output level consistent with full employment (natural rate of unemployment)', 'The GDP level before any recession', 'The GDP predicted by the government\'s budget']),
